Czech Stock Index Rises From 2-Year Low as CEZ, Telefonica Gain

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-09-14T12:05:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-14/czech-stock-index-rises-from-2-year-low-as-telefonica-cme-gain.html
The Czech  stock index  rebounded
from its lowest in more than two years as Telefonica Czech
Republic AS,  CEZ AS (CEZ)  and  Central European Media Enterprises Ltd. (CETV) 
advanced, outweighing declines at New World Resources Plc.  The PX gauge of 14 companies added 1.2 percent to 957.7 as
of 1:56 p.m. in Prague. The benchmark slumped 6 percent in the
previous three days to its lowest close since July 2009.  Stocks in Europe and U.S. index futures rose on speculation
China may still buy bonds of Europe’s most-indebted nations.
France will “do everything to save Greece,” Valerie Pecresse,
spokeswoman to the government, said after a cabinet meeting
today. Greek Prime Minister  George Papandreou  is due to discuss
ways to avert the nation’s default with German Chancellor  Angela
Merkel  and French President  Nicolas Sarkozy  later today.  “European equities reversed earlier losses after more
supportive comments from European Union politicians appeared to
deflect the risk of a disorderly Greece default,” analysts at
Brown Brothers Harriman & Co. wrote in an e-mail to clients.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
